2022 Highlights! 🗓️ This year was honestly so fulfilling for me, especially after these last two crazy years we’ve all had. Also dove deep into a bunch of  different hobbies this year which have been super fun. Highly recommend picking up new things every once in a while. Stoked for the the future - the sky is the limit!

This clip is from our trip to Europe for the @eukendamachamp!

@matt_sweets, @codygriz, and I were supposed to do the whole trip together (Paris -> Amsterdam -> Leiden) but I was delayed about 3 days due to flight complications 🥲 So I was pretty bummed because I was so excited to see France with everyone. I took French in high school and couldn’t wait to see if I recognized any of the language or culture.

So I finally get to France and Sweets and Cody were already on the way to Amsterdam to see @supernog73. I was expecting to miss France and have to get on a train right away to meet up with the boys, but luckily the plan changed and I got to have a day in Paris riding around with @pj_martini_reno. Finally got to hang out at the Eiffel Tower and got a couple clips to commemorate the moment. 

The full Sweets Life Vlog is on the @sweetskendamas YouTube channel so you can see the whole journey!

The process behind the Straps (kendama holder keychain clips).
Step 1: Cutting strips from the LV printed canvas
Step2: Gluing the fabric onto the rubber lined elastic for grippy-ness.
Step 3: Had to put masking tape under the rubber part so the straps would feed through my sewing machine.
Step 4: Sewing the straps.
Step 5: Using a hot metal semicircle tool, cut/melt the edges of the straps to eliminate fraying.
Step 6: Mark where your hardware holes need to be and hole punch them out.

Stay tuned for the rest of the process to see the final product!
